&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 5/7 Rota -37.5 hrs .&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The above hours are worked Monday – Sunday - subject to the needs of the department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require an enthusiastic individual who can work within the Portering Services team at the Central Campus RHH and offer flexibility to cover all&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Portering related tasks including Charge-hand and driving duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should be educated to GCSE grade D or above (or equivalent) have good communication skills and able to use own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comprehensive in-house training and uniform will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job role requires a flexible approach to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Full driving licence required - &lt;/em&gt;Licences issued after 1.1.97 will need the following categories in addition to standard licence:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B+E, categories C1 and D1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to the nature of this role, successful candidates will be required to complete a DBS disclosure application (Police check).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrew Stacey -Portering Manager&lt;/p&gt;
